== Welcome to url.markr

* Homepage: http://urlmarkr.rubyforge.net
* Author: Joey Walsh
* Email: nemonoid@rubyforge.org
* Version: 20060517
* Copyright: Joey Walsh
* License: GNU GPL

url.markr is a personal bookmark manager written in Ruby on Rails. It has support for tagging of bookmarks, RSS feeds of links for each tag, inline editing of bookmarks and tag autocompletion on entering a new bookmark. You can also import your existing del.icio.us bookmarks into url.markr.

==Requirements

    * Ruby 1.8.2 or higher
    * Rails 1.1
    * acts_as_taggable ruby gem (gem install acts_as_taggable)
    * MySQL with Ruby bindings
    * Firefox 1.5+ (not yet tested on other browsers)

== Getting started

1. Checkout the source code or download the tarball.
2. Create database called urlmarkr. Create the database schema using db/urlmarkr.sql
3. Edit config/database.yml.orig to reflect your database configuration and save as config/database.yml
4. Edit config/environment.rb to suit your settings (see http://urlmarkr.nemonoid.org/urlmarkr/wiki/FAQ)
5. Start the web server: ruby script/server webrick (run with --help for options)
6. Go to http://localhost:3000/ and your on your way!

You can easily bookmark pages using the Bookmarklet found under the options menu. Simply drag it too your bookmarks toolbar for easy access.

